node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Top Luxuries on July 14, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text:
A once-in-a-lifetime experience! Credit @michaeldbliss. 🌋 

"There’s not really a good way to describe what we saw this night. Pictures are the closest way but they still don’t do this experience justice. The volcano erupted every 10-15 minutes and we had front row seats. We stayed here for 8 hours watching this and the last eruption we saw was as exciting and unbelievable as the first."

📸 @michaeldbliss
📍 Fagradalsfjall, Iceland

node.text:
Navigating the maze of floating icebergs with @aleixsalvat in Jökulsárlón, the deepest lake in Iceland with a depth of about 250 meters (820 feet). 🧊

Jökulsárlón literally translates to "glacial river lagoon". Its icebergs are made up of age-old glacial ice, which means that they may be 1,000 years old. For an immersive experience, visitors can go on boat tours or kayak on the lagoon. Notably, what's special about Jokulsarlon is its everchanging landscape, making every visit to the lagoon unique.

Would you kayak here? 🇮🇸

📽 @aleixsalvat
📍 Jökulsárlón, Iceland
🎶 An Air for Bethlehem / A Gift for the King - MPK Christian Celtic Band
